Former Vice President, Atiku Abubakar, has reacted to the death of ex-Ogun East Senator, Buruji Kashamu. Buruji Kashamu was said to have died of COVID-19 on Saturday. Reacting, Atiku on Twitter, prayed that his soul Rest In Peace. He said, “My thoughts and prayers are with the family and friends of late Senator Buruji Kashamu. “May the Almighty Allah accept his soul, forgive his shortcomings and heal the loved ones he left behind.”